title: JPMorgan sees $1 trillion flowing into the stock market in 2021 amid 'one of the best environments' in years

title: A positive feedback loop is set to drive stocks higher in 2021, JPMorgan's quant guru says
text: A decline in volatility will drive a positive feedback loop that drives the stock market higher in 2021, according to a Wednesday note from JPMorgan's quant strategist Marko Kolanovic. The bank, which expects the S&P 500 to rise as much as 25% next year, sees a marked declined in volatility given a high level of monetary accommodation from central banks around the globe in response to the COVID-19 pandemic.

title: Wheat futures set for highest finish in nearly two weeks as USDA lowers U.S. ending stocks estimate
text: Wheat futures climbed on Thursday, setting prices up for their highest finish in nearly two weeks after a monthly report from the U.S. Department of Agriculture revealed a lower estimate for domestic 2020/2021 ending stocks. The USDA cut its outlook for wheat ending stocks by 15 million bushels to 862 million bushels, which would be down 16% from the previous marketing year.
